# Paths listed here are copied from the main checkout into a freshly created
# jj workspace by the WorktreeCreate hook (claude-worktree-create.sh in the
# jj skill). Directories are deep-copied via APFS clone where supported, so
# the initial copy is near-zero disk and stays cheap until divergence.
#
# Git submodules — jj does not manage submodules itself, so these directories
# would otherwise be empty in a new workspace and any Xcode target that
# references them (currently the WireGuardBridgeiOS legacy build target for
# Dev / FamilyDev) would fail to build. Mocked / FamilyMocked do not need
# them.
deps/wireguard-apple
deps/translate
deps/landing-github-pages
